He was... He was a very decisive person. He had 
strong opinions,

29:12.572 --> 29:27.469
made judgments quickly about people, some of 
which I thought were very astute and some of which I

29:12.572 --> 29:27.469
thought were considerably off-mark. I thought 
the same about my judgment. But were there some key

29:32.634 --> 29:37.680
decisions about liberal arts and or education, 
which you now look back and see those were

29:39.112 --> 29:47.782
important decisions, plus or minus. Well, I think 
